title: How to Make Cinnamon and Walnut Pumpkin Cake

steps.headline: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
Grease and flour the 12x18 inch pan.
Sieve together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, intermix the sugar and oil.
Integrate vanilla and pumpkin, then beat in eggs one at a time.
Bit by bit, whisk in the flour mixture.
Spread batter into prepared 12x18 inch pan.
Bake it in the oven for 30 minutes, or until a toothpick put into the center of the cake comes out clean.

text: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).  Grease and flour the 12x18 inch pan.  Sieve together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Set it aside. In a large bowl, intermix the sugar and oil.  Integrate vanilla and pumpkin, then beat in eggs one at a time.  Bit by bit, whisk in the flour mixture.  Stir in nuts.  Spread batter into prepared 12x18 inch pan.  Bake it in the oven for 30 minutes, or until a toothpick put into the center of the cake comes out clean.  Allow it to cool.
